          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A method is developed in which pulse-height spectra",
                "from plastic scintillator are carefully analysed to",
                "give the total number of low pulse height events",
                "obtained with a mono-energetic incident beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The thin dE/dx crystal was chosen for each",
                "particular incident energy to give an energy loss of",
                "300 keV, which produced a spectrum resolution of",
                "about 25%. The material used was Nuclear Enterprise's",
                "NE 102 plastic scintillator. The crystal was mounted",
                "on an EMI 6097B photomultiplier.",
                "The full energy detector was also made of Ne 102,",
                "7.6 cm in diameter by 3.8 cm thick and this was mated",
                " to an EMI 6097F photomultiplier."
              ]
            }
          ],
